==Chinese==

===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|口|十|ls=psc|c1=s|c2=p}} – an ancient variant form of {{och-l|協|to cooperate}} used since antiquity.

It was later borrowed for {{m|zh|葉}} because {{m|zh|協}} and {{m|zh|葉}} are homophones in some varieties of Northern {{cog|wuu|-}}. This usage was made official in Simplified Chinese.

